```scala
case class Foo(d: Double) extends AnyVal
null.asInstanceOf[Foo]
```

```scala
java.lang.NullPointerException
	at .<init>(<console>:10)
	at .<clinit>(<console>)
	at .<init>(<console>:7)
	at .<clinit>(<console>)
	at $print(<console>)
```

This behavior is problematic because code in the standard library relies on the fact that casting null to a type returns the "default" value of this type (as specified in ยง4.2):

